article.description: Rahmon Fletcher scored 20 points and Alec Brown had a double-double Saturday as Wisconsin-Green Bay kept Illinois-Chicago winless in the Horizon League.
article.headline: Green Bay keeps UIC winless in Horizon play
article.linkText: Green Bay keeps UIC winless in Horizon play
article.story: GREEN BAY, Wis. -- Rahmon Fletcher scored 20 points and Alec Brown had a double-double Saturday as Wisconsin-Green Bay kept Illinois-Chicago winless in the Horizon League with a 74-50 victory. Fletcher's output included three 3-pointers, and Brown had 11 points and 10 rebounds for the Phoenix (10-9, 4-3), which won its fourth straight game. Bryquis Perine added 16 points and a game-best five assists. Paul Carter had 11 points and 10 rebounds for the Flames (5-14, 0-7), who went 0-for-12 from 3-point range as they lost their seventh in a row. Brad Birton scored 12 points. The Phoenix shot 46.7 percent (28 of 60) and 40.0 percent (8 of 20) on 3-pointers. The Flames shot just 39.2 percent (20 of 51). Wisconsin-Green Bay led 42-22 at the break.
